  "summaries": [
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":1,"summary":"David learns of Saul and Jonathan's deaths, executes the Amalekite messenger, and composes a lament for the fallen."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":2,"summary":"David is anointed king of Judah at Hebron while Ish-bosheth rules Israel; civil war begins with the battle at Gibeon where Asahel is killed."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":3,"summary":"Abner defects from Ish-bosheth to David but is killed by Joab; David publicly mourns Abner to prove his innocence."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":4,"summary":"Ish-bosheth is assassinated by Rechab and Baanah; David executes them for murdering an innocent man."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":5,"summary":"All Israel anoints David king at Hebron; he captures Jerusalem as his capital and defeats the Philistines twice with divine direction."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":6,"summary":"David brings the Ark to Jerusalem with celebration; Uzzah is struck dead for touching it, and Michal despises David for dancing."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":7,"summary":"David desires to build a temple, but God through Nathan establishes the Davidic Covenant, promising an everlasting throne; David prays in humility."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":8,"summary":"David defeats the Philistines, Moabites, Syrians, and Edomites, expanding his kingdom and dedicating the spoils to the Lord."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":9,"summary":"David shows kindness to Mephibosheth, son of Jonathan, restoring Saul's lands and granting him a permanent place at the royal table."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":10,"summary":"The Ammonites humiliate David's ambassadors; Joab and Abishai defeat the combined Ammonite-Syrian forces in battle."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":11,"summary":"David commits adultery with Bathsheba, fails to cover his sin through Uriah, and arranges Uriah's death in battle."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":12,"summary":"Nathan confronts David with the parable of the ewe lamb; David repents, the child dies, and Solomon is born to Bathsheba."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":13,"summary":"Amnon violates his half-sister Tamar; Absalom waits two years then has Amnon killed at a feast and flees to Geshur."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":14,"summary":"Joab uses the wise woman of Tekoa to persuade David to recall Absalom from exile, though Absalom remains barred from the king's presence."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":15,"summary":"Absalom conspires to steal the kingdom through four years of political manipulation; David flees Jerusalem weeping over the Mount of Olives."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":16,"summary":"Ziba brings provisions and slanders Mephibosheth; Shimei curses David; Absalom enters Jerusalem and follows Ahithophel's counsel."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":17,"summary":"Hushai defeats Ahithophel's counsel to attack David immediately; Ahithophel hangs himself and David escapes across the Jordan."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":18,"summary":"David's forces defeat Absalom's army in the forest of Ephraim; Joab kills Absalom, and David mourns bitterly for his son."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":19,"summary":"Joab rebukes David's mourning; David returns to Jerusalem, pardons Shimei, and navigates disputes among Judah and Israel."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":20,"summary":"Sheba leads a revolt against David; Joab pursues him, and the wise woman of Abel delivers Sheba's head to end the rebellion."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":21,"summary":"A three-year famine is traced to Saul's bloodguilt against the Gibeonites; David delivers Saul's descendants, and wars with Philistine giants follow."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":22,"summary":"David's great psalm of deliverance, praising God as his rock, fortress, and shield who delivered him from all his enemies."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":23,"summary":"David's last prophetic words and the catalog of his mighty men with their legendary feats of valor and loyalty."},
    {"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":24,"summary":"David numbers the people against Joab's counsel; God sends a plague as judgment, and David purchases Araunah's threshingfloor to build an altar."}
  ],
